"title": "5956: strength, human",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5956: strength, human",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>All human strength derives from God. Among non-believers, strength may become a source of arrogant self-confidence, the oppression of others or rebellion against God.</p>\n<h2>The strength of the ungodly</h2>\n<h3>Physical prowess</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:4-1Sam17:10\">1SA 17:4–17:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:31-Num13:33\">NUM 13:31–13:33</a></p>\n<h3>Intelligence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:22\">1CO 1:22</a></strong> <em>The Gentile world relies on fallen reason rather than revelation.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:19-Acts17:21\">ACT 17:19–17:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Political and military might</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:7\">PSA 20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:8-Gen10:12\">GEN 10:8–10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:16\">PSA 33:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:18-Isa36:20\">ISA 36:18–36:20</a></p>\n<h3>Prosperity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:6\">PSA 49:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:4\">JER 49:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:19\">LUK 12:18–12:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17\">1TI 6:17</a></p>\n<h2>The ultimate futility of human strength</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:7-2Chr32:8\">2CH 32:7–32:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:17\">PSA 49:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:3\">PSA 146:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:15\">ECC 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:3\">ISA 30:1–30:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:20\">LUK 12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:19-1Cor1:20\">1CO 1:19–1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:6\">1CO 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:7\">1TI 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:11\">JAS 1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Negative consequences of human strength</h2>\n<h3>Arrogant self-confidence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:4\">GEN 11:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:41-1Sam17:44\">1SA 17:41–17:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:1\">PSA 52:1</a> <em>Boasting betrays the source of people's confidence</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:8-Isa36:9\">ISA 36:8–36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:30\">DAN 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:12\">LUK 18:9–18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:13\">GAL 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>Violence and oppression</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:7\">PSA 52:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:23-Gen4:24\">GEN 4:23–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:11-Exod1:14\">EXO 1:11–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:10-Exod5:14\">EXO 5:10–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:2\">JDG 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:6\">JDG 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:14\">PSA 37:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:3-Ps73:8\">PSA 73:3–73:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8\">ISA 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4-Jas5:6\">JAS 5:4–5:6</a></p>\n<h2>The physical strength of some godly men</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:20\">2SA 23:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:22\">1CH 11:22</a> <em>Benaiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:20-1Chr11:21\">1CH 11:20–11:21</a> <em>Abishai</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:32-Heb11:34\">HEB 11:32–11:34</a></p>",
